<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<LinearLayout xmlns:android="http://schemas.android.com/apk/res/android"
        android:layout_width="match_parent"
        android:layout_height="match_parent"
        android:orientation="vertical"
        android:padding="16dp">

    <LinearLayout
            android:layout_width="match_parent"
            android:layout_height="wrap_content">

        <Button
                android:id="@+id/start_log"
                android:layout_width="wrap_content"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:layout_weight="0.50"
                android:text="@string/start_logging" />

        <Button
                android:id="@+id/stop_log"
                android:layout_width="wrap_content"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:layout_weight="0.50"
                android:text="@string/stop_logging" />
    </LinearLayout>

    <LinearLayout
            android:layout_width="match_parent"
            android:layout_height="wrap_content">

        <Button
                android:id="@+id/copy_to_clipboard"
                android:layout_width="wrap_content"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:layout_weight="0.50"
                android:text="@string/copy_to_clipboard" />

        <Button
                android:id="@+id/save_to_file"
                android:layout_width="wrap_content"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:layout_weight="0.50"
                android:text="@string/dump_logcat" />
    </LinearLayout>

    <Button
            android:id="@+id/clear_log"
            android:layout_width="match_parent"
            android:layout_height="wrap_content"
            android:text="@string/clear_log" />

    <!-- 
      =====================================================================================
      WAVE 1 HOST MIGRATION - DebugLogActivity (task compose-2l4.1.2)
      VLCComposeView embedded directly inside legacy XML layout (debug_log.xml).

      This is Pattern #1 (see NetworkServerDialog / network_server_dialog.xml as exact template).

      - The tag is a normal custom view; no dataBinding or special inflation needed.
      - In Kotlin host (see DebugLogActivity.kt): 
            val composeHost = findViewById<VLCComposeView>(R.id.compose_interop_debuglog_demo)
            composeHost.setContent {
                VLCTheme {
                    VLCDebugLogLine(text = "Compose-powered log line (interop demo)")
                }
            }

      BEFORE (legacy): debug_log_item.xml (trivial 5-line monospace TextView) inflated by
                       ArrayAdapter<String> for the ListView log rows. STILL FULLY PRESERVED.
      AFTER (demo + migration): Legacy ArrayAdapter path + debug_log_item.xml remain 100%
                                compilable and available (additive only; see comments in .kt).
                                + Live Compose rendering of VLCDebugLogLine appears here as
                                  header demo + (via custom adapter row pattern) for actual log lines.

      Hybrid migration strategy notes (copy-paste for future Wave 1+ hosts):
      * Leaf Composables (VLCDebugLogLine, VLCDropdownItem, VLCInfoItem, ...) are safe to host
        immediately: zero side effects, self-contained, wrap their own VLCTheme (or accept explicit).
      * Two patterns (both used in this host):
          1. Layout XML + findViewById<VLCComposeView> + setContent { VLCTheme { Leaf(...) } }
          2. Programmatic: ComposeView(context) inside custom adapter getView() for list rows.
      * Original XML layouts (debug_log_item.xml) are preserved during + after demonstration.
        Rollback: delete the new id usage + view tag + new adapter class + 5 imports;
                  the ListView + old ArrayAdapter line continue to function exactly as before.
      * For lists: the small Compose-based row adapter below demonstrates the bridge for
        ArrayAdapter/ListView/RecyclerView hosts. (Full migration of this screen would later
        replace ListView entirely with LazyColumn inside a Compose screen.)
      * Theming: light/dark via VLCTheme + isSystemInDarkTheme() (or explicit). Matches
        Material3 bodySmall + Monospace. Previews in PreviewUtils.kt + VLCDebugLogLine.kt
        verify both modes.
      * Permanent Exceptions boundary: This host (debug log viewer) is fully migratable;
        contrast with native player surfaces, complex MediaLibrary JNI, certain TV overlays,
        or WebView-based legacy that stay outside Compose forever.
      * Wave 1 epic / traceability: This is the first real post-demo Wave 1 host migration
        (compose-2l4.1.2). Reference implementation: compose-5qk (NetworkServerDialog.kt +
        network_server_dialog.xml). See also: compose-5wg (bd), VLCDebugLogLine.kt,
        VLCCompose.kt, VLCTheme.kt, and cross-cutting notes (compose-2l4.1.8).

      See also: application/compose/src/main/java/org/videolan/vlc/compose/components/DebugLogLine.kt
                application/compose/src/main/java/org/videolan/vlc/compose/interop/VLCCompose.kt
                application/vlc-android/src/org/videolan/vlc/gui/dialogs/NetworkServerDialog.kt
      =====================================================================================
    -->
    <org.videolan.vlc.compose.interop.VLCComposeView
            android:id="@+id/compose_interop_debuglog_demo"
            android:layout_width="match_parent"
            android:layout_height="wrap_content"
            android:layout_marginTop="8dp"
            android:layout_marginBottom="4dp" />

    <ListView
            android:id="@+id/log_list"
            android:layout_width="match_parent"
            android:layout_height="wrap_content"
            android:paddingTop="10dip" />

</LinearLayout>
